---
const GH = 'https://github.com/olagopirez/sextante';
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
  <title>sextante — MPU-9250 driver for Raspberry Pi</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Attitude and heading from a 9-axis IMU. A Python driver for the InvenSense MPU-9250 on the Raspberry Pi — tested without hardware, documented down to the silicon." />
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/favicon.svg`} />
  <meta property="og:title" content="sextante" />
  <meta property="og:description" content="Attitude and heading from a 9-axis IMU. Python driver for the MPU-9250 on the Raspberry Pi." />
</head>
<body>
  <header class="statusbar">
    <span class="brand">⌖ SEXTANTE <span class="dim">// IMU DRIVER</span></span>
    <nav>
      <a href="#quickstart">QUICK START</a>
      <a href={`${GH}/blob/master/docs/hardware.md`}>HARDWARE</a>
      <a href={`${GH}/blob/master/docs/architecture.md`}>ARCHITECTURE</a>
      <a href={GH}>GITHUB ↗</a>
    </nav>
    <span class="sys"><span class="dot"></span> SYS ONLINE · v0.2</span>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-copy">
        <p class="kicker">// ATTITUDE &amp; HEADING SYSTEM</p>
        <h1>SEXTANTE</h1>
        <p class="sub">
          A Python driver for the InvenSense <strong>MPU-9250</strong> — accelerometer,
          gyroscope and AK8963 magnetometer over I2C on the Raspberry Pi.
          Tested without hardware. Documented down to the silicon.
        </p>
        <div class="panel boot">
          <header class="panel-title">SELF-CHECK</header>
          <pre id="boot"></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="cta">
          <a class="btn primary" href="#quickstart">QUICK START</a>
          <a class="btn" href={GH}>VIEW ON GITHUB</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-scene">
        <div class="scene-frame">
          <canvas id="scene"></canvas>
          <div class="panel telemetry">
            <header class="panel-title">TELEMETRY <span class="live"><span class="dot"></span> LIVE</span></header>
            <div class="t-rows">
              <div class="t-row"><span class="lbl">GYRO</span><span class="unit">°/s</span>
                <b data-t="g1"></b><b data-t="g2"></b><b data-t="g3"></b></div>
              <div class="t-row"><span class="lbl">ACCEL</span><span class="unit">g</span>
                <b data-t="a1"></b><b data-t="a2"></b><b data-t="a3"></b></div>
              <div class="t-row"><span class="lbl">MAG</span><span class="unit">µT</span>
                <b data-t="m1"></b><b data-t="m2"></b><b data-t="m3"></b></div>
              <div class="t-row"><span class="lbl">TEMP</span><span class="unit">°C</span>
                <b data-t="temp"></b></div>
            </div>
            <footer class="t-foot">WHO_AM_I 0x71 · WIA 0x48 · 50 Hz</footer>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="scene-hint">
          DRAG THE CUBE — BODY-FRAME AXES, AS THE DRIVER REPORTS THEM
          <button id="imu-btn" hidden>USE MY PHONE'S IMU</button>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="features">
      <h2>// NINE AXES, DONE RIGHT</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="panel">
          <h3>REAL MAGNETOMETER DATA</h3>
          <p>The AK8963 runs in continuous 16-bit mode (0.15 µT/LSB); every sample is
          validity-gated by the ST1/ST2 status registers. Actual microteslas, not noise.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="panel">
          <h3>HARDWARE SELF-CHECK</h3>
          <p><code>WHO_AM_I</code> and the magnetometer id are verified before configuring
          anything — relabeled MPU-6500 boards get diagnosed, not silently tolerated.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="panel">
          <h3>ONE FRAME FOR EVERYTHING</h3>
          <p>Magnetometer readings are remapped into the accel/gyro body frame, so heading
          and fusion math get consistent axes out of the box.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="panel">
          <h3>BACKGROUND SAMPLING</h3>
          <p>A drift-free ticker samples at your rate; <code>get_avg()</code> synchronously
          returns the average of everything since the previous call.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="panel">
          <h3>TEST WITHOUT HARDWARE</h3>
          <p>The I2C bus is injectable — the whole test suite runs against an in-memory
          fake, on any machine, in under a second.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="panel">
          <h3>DOCUMENTED INTERNALS</h3>
          <p>Two dies, two byte orders, two access modes — the
          <a href={`${GH}/blob/master/docs/hardware.md`}>hardware doc</a> explains the chip
          the datasheets assume you already understand.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="quickstart" class="quickstart">
      <h2>// QUICK START</h2>
      <pre class="panel"><code><span class="c"># On the Raspberry Pi (I2C enabled)</span>
git clone {GH}.git
cd sextante
pip install -e .</code></pre>
      <pre class="panel"><code><span class="k">import</span> time
<span class="k">from</span> mpu9250 <span class="k">import</span> MPU9250

mpu = MPU9250(rate=<span class="n">50</span>)
mpu.initialize()   <span class="c"># self-checks the chip, calibrates, starts sampling</span>

<span class="k">while</span> <span class="k">True</span>:
    time.sleep(<span class="n">1</span>)
    print(mpu.get_avg().get_json())   <span class="c"># °/s, g, µT, °C</span></code></pre>
      <p class="hint">At rest you should see <code>A3 ≈ 1.0</code> (gravity), gyros ≈ 0 and a
      realistic temperature — a five-second wiring sanity check.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="whoami">
      <h2>// IS YOUR CHIP REAL?</h2>
      <p>The MPU-9250 is discontinued and heavily counterfeited. <code>self_check()</code>
      reads <code>WHO_AM_I</code> and tells you what you actually own:</p>
      <table class="panel">
        <thead><tr><th><code>WHO_AM_I</code></th><th>CHIP</th><th>VERDICT</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>0x71</code></td><td>MPU-9250</td><td class="ok">GENUINE ✓</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>0x73</code></td><td>MPU-9255</td><td class="ok">WORKS FINE ✓</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>0x70</code></td><td>MPU-6500</td><td class="warn">RELABEL — NO MAGNETOMETER</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>0x68</code></td><td>MPU-6050</td><td class="bad">DIFFERENT PART</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p><a href={`${GH}/blob/master/docs/hardware.md#identification-is-your-chip-real`}>
      THE FULL STORY OF THE TWO DIES →</a></p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="statusbar foot">
    <span>MIT © OSCAR LAGO</span>
    <a href={GH}>GITHUB.COM/OLAGOPIREZ/SEXTANTE</a>
    <span class="sys"><span class="dot"></span> SYS NOMINAL</span>
  </footer>

  <script>
    import { initScene } from '../scripts/scene.js';
    import { typeBoot, startTelemetry } from '../scripts/hud.js';

    const state = initScene(document.getElementById('scene'), document.getElementById('imu-btn'));
    startTelemetry(document, state);
    typeBoot(document.getElementById('boot'), [
      '> sextante v0.2 — boot',
      '> bus ............. I2C-1 @ 400 kHz',
      '> WHO_AM_I ........ 0x71 · MPU-9250 ✓',
      '> AK8963 WIA ...... 0x48 ✓',
      '> fuse ROM ASA .... 178 · 182 · 171',
      '> magnetometer .... continuous · 100 Hz · 16-bit',
      '> sampling ........ 50 Hz · running',
    ]);
  </script>

  <style is:global>
    :root {
      --bg: #02060d;
      --holo: #35e0ff;
      --holo-dim: rgba(53, 224, 255, 0.28);
      --holo-faint: rgba(53, 224, 255, 0.09);
      --panel: rgba(6, 18, 32, 0.72);
      --text: #c9e7f2;
      --muted: #6f93a8;
      --ok: #31f27b;
      --warn: #ffb547;
      --bad: #ff5f5f;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
    body {
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--text);
      font: 14.5px/1.65 ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', 'Cascadia Code', Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
      background:
        radial-gradient(900px 520px at 72% -6%, rgba(53, 224, 255, 0.08), transparent 60%),
        linear-gradient(rgba(53, 224, 255, 0.035) 1px, transparent 1px) 0 0 / 100% 44px,
        linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(53, 224, 255, 0.035) 1px, transparent 1px) 0 0 / 44px 100%,
        var(--bg);
    }
    body::after {
      content: '';
      position: fixed; inset: 0; z-index: 999; pointer-events: none;
      background: repeating-linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.012) 0 1px, transparent 1px 3px);
    }
    a { color: var(--holo); text-decoration: none; }
    a:hover { text-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--holo-dim); }
    code { color: #9feaff; }

    .dot {
      display: inline-block; width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%;
      background: var(--ok); box-shadow: 0 0 6px var(--ok);
      animation: blink 1.8s steps(2) infinite;
    }
    @keyframes blink { 50% { opacity: 0.25; } }

    .statusbar {
      display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; gap: 16px;
      max-width: 1120px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 14px 24px;
      font-size: 0.82em; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--holo-faint);
    }
    .statusbar .brand { color: var(--holo); font-weight: 700; }
    .statusbar .dim { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 400; }
    .statusbar nav { display: flex; gap: 18px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .statusbar nav a { color: var(--muted); }
    .statusbar nav a:hover { color: var(--text); }
    .statusbar .sys { color: var(--ok); white-space: nowrap; }
    .statusbar.foot { border-top: 1px solid var(--holo-faint); border-bottom: none; margin-top: 70px; color: var(--muted); }

    main { max-width: 1120px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px 40px; }

    .panel {
      position: relative;
      background: var(--panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--holo-dim);
      backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
    }
    .panel::before, .panel::after {
      content: ''; position: absolute; width: 13px; height: 13px;
      border-style: solid; border-color: var(--holo);
    }
    .panel::before { top: -1px; left: -1px; border-width: 2px 0 0 2px; }
    .panel::after { bottom: -1px; right: -1px; border-width: 0 2px 2px 0; }
    .panel-title {
      display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;
      padding: 7px 12px; font-size: 0.74em; letter-spacing: 0.22em; color: var(--holo);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--holo-faint);
    }

    .hero {
      display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.15fr; gap: 30px;
      align-items: center; padding: 44px 0 8px;
    }
    .kicker { color: var(--holo); letter-spacing: 0.24em; font-size: 0.78em; margin: 0 0 4px; }
    .hero h1 {
      margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 3.1em; letter-spacing: 0.26em; color: #eaffff;
      text-shadow: 0 0 22px rgba(53, 224, 255, 0.45);
    }
    .sub { color: var(--muted); max-width: 46ch; margin: 0 0 18px; }
    .sub strong { color: var(--text); }

    .boot pre {
      margin: 0; padding: 12px 14px; font-size: 0.82em; line-height: 1.7;
      color: #8fe8fa; min-height: 9.5em; white-space: pre-wrap;
    }
    .cta { display: flex; gap: 12px; margin-top: 20px; }
    .btn {
      padding: 10px 18px; border: 1px solid var(--holo-dim); color: var(--holo);
      font-size: 0.82em; letter-spacing: 0.14em; background: transparent;
    }
    .btn:hover { background: var(--holo-faint); box-shadow: 0 0 16px rgba(53, 224, 255, 0.25); text-shadow: none; }
    .btn.primary { background: rgba(53, 224, 255, 0.16); border-color: var(--holo); }

    .hero-scene { min-width: 0; }
    .scene-frame { position: relative; }
    #scene {
      width: 100%; height: 460px; display: block; cursor: grab;
      border: 1px solid var(--holo-faint);
    }
    #scene:active { cursor: grabbing; }
    .scene-hint {
      text-align: center; color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.72em;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em; margin-top: 8px;
    }
    #imu-btn {
      margin-left: 10px; padding: 4px 10px; cursor: pointer;
      background: var(--holo-faint); color: var(--holo);
      border: 1px solid var(--holo-dim); font: inherit; letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    }

    .telemetry {
      position: absolute; top: 12px; right: 12px; width: 248px; font-size: 11.5px;
    }
    .telemetry .live { color: var(--ok); letter-spacing: 0.1em; display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center; }
    .t-rows { padding: 8px 12px; }
    .t-row { display: flex; gap: 7px; align-items: baseline; line-height: 1.9; }
    .t-row .lbl { color: var(--holo); width: 44px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
    .t-row .unit { color: var(--muted); width: 24px; font-size: 0.9em; }
    .t-row b {
      font-weight: 400; width: 51px; text-align: right; color: #dffaff;
      text-shadow: 0 0 7px rgba(53, 224, 255, 0.35); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    }
    .t-foot {
      padding: 6px 12px; border-top: 1px solid var(--holo-faint);
      color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.86em; letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    }

    section { margin-top: 66px; }
    h2 { font-size: 1.25em; letter-spacing: 0.24em; color: var(--holo); font-weight: 600; }

    .grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 14px; }
    .grid article { padding: 16px 18px; }
    .grid h3 { margin: 0 0 8px; font-size: 0.82em; letter-spacing: 0.16em; color: var(--holo); }
    .grid p { margin: 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.94em; }

    pre.panel { padding: 16px 18px; overflow-x: auto; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 0.95em; }
    pre .c { color: #52708a; }
    pre .k { color: #7dd3fc; }
    pre .n { color: var(--warn); }
    .hint { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.9em; }

    table.panel { border-collapse: separate; border-spacing: 0; width: 100%; max-width: 620px; }
    th, td { text-align: left; padding: 9px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--holo-faint); }
    th { color: var(--holo); font-size: 0.78em; letter-spacing: 0.18em; }
    tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    td.ok { color: var(--ok); }
    td.warn { color: var(--warn); }
    td.bad { color: var(--bad); }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .hero { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .hero h1 { font-size: 2.3em; }
      #scene { height: 340px; }
      .telemetry { position: static; width: auto; margin-top: 10px; }
      .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .statusbar { flex-wrap: wrap; }
    }
  </style>
</body>
</html>
